#N Gosper Glider Gun
#C The first known finite pattern with infinite growth. Emits one glider
#C every 30 generations (period-30). In digital logic, a glider gun acts
#C as a clock signal or constant "1" source. Two guns can be collided to
#C produce a period-60 stream representing a 1-bit wire.
#C Discovered by Bill Gosper in November 1970.
x = 36, y = 9, rule = B3/S23
